  The Bigger Picture                                                                                                                                        
                    
  Every one of these runs is proving that a completely custom hybrid SSM/Transformer architecture with a full internal life dynamics system can train stably
   from scratch via distillation. No pretrained backbone. No shortcuts. The Life Equation infrastructure — temporal dynamics, homeostasis, fatigue,         
  identity, episodic memory, purpose conflict, self-viability — is all wired correctly and computing clean gradients. The controller makes decisions every
  step. Forensic bundles are saved. Checkpoints resume cleanly.                                                                                             
                  
  The maturity gate failures are not failures of the idea. They're calibration problems that have corresponding solutions: logit biases for behavioral      
  correction, hard gates for safety floors, and the fundamental prediction error metric that will resolve as training continues into the tens of thousands
  of steps that distillation requires.                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                 
